# special role showcase

## Summary

Displays a scrolling list of names in an overlay window.

## Setup

- Define the custom role for these groups. E.g. Keep of the Forge
- Setup a new Channel Reward. Set a reward name and a meaningful description.
- Manage effects for when the reward is purchased:
  - Update Viewer Roles, add user to role
  - Set user metadata
    - `$math[$userMetadata[$user, forgeKeeperCount] + 1]`
    - in this example, forgeKeeperCount is being used to manage how many times a user has purchased this role.

That is all for settings, now to to setup the command to show the list of special role users

- First, setup a command to clear this list. This is a good 'oh shit' measure if something goes wrong.
  - Add command, Clear Effects, and select 'Overlay Effects'
- Create a new command used to show the list. E.g. !keepersList

Add an 'Evaluate JavaScript' effect

```js
// gets a list of the first 100 users with forgeKeepCount metadata
const keepers = $rawTopMetadata["forgeKeeperCount", 100] 
// format the list of data to formatted string of data
const list = keepers.reduce((acc,data) => acc + `${data.userDisplayName} ${data.amount}x\\n`, '');
// return the data
return list
```

// Output variable used: `$effectOutput[keepersList]`

Add a 'Show HTML' Effect

Note, my html skills are weak, but this looked acceptable.

- Show diration: 15 seconds
- Enter: 'Fade In'
- INBETWEEN: 'None'
- Exit: 'Fade Out'

```html
<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lora:ital,wght@0,400..700;1,400..700&display=swap');
  .scroll-container {
    width: 600px;
    height: 650px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.95);
    border: 2px solid #FFFFFF;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    padding: 10px;
    margin-left: 200px;
    margin-top: 150px;
  }
  .title {
    color: #ffffff;
    font-family: "Lora", sans-serif;
    font-size: 56px;
    font-weight: 400;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #ffffff;
    padding-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .scroll-viewport {
    position: relative;
    flex: 1 1 auto;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-top: 10px;
  }
  .scroll-content {
    color: #ffffff;
    font-size: 48px;
    font-family: "Lora", sans-serif;
   font-weight:400; 
    line-height: 1.4;
    white-space: pre-line;
    text-align: center;
    animation: scroll-up 15s linear infinite;
  }
  @keyframes scroll-up {
    0% {
      transform: translateY(75%);
    }
    100% {
      transform: translateY(-95%);
    }
  }
</style>

<div class="scroll-container">
  <div class="title">Keepers of the Forge</div>
  <div class="scroll-viewport">
    <div class="scroll-content">
      $effectOutput[keepersList]
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

```
